{"TopicId":193177,"ForumId":109,"TopicTitle":"Developer Insights #3","CreatedByName":"MechBFP","CreatedById":184845,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-16T17:00:36Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"MechBFP","CreatedById":184845,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-16T17:00:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSee the link below:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.kerbalspaceprogram.com/dev-diaries/developer-insights-3-ksp2-design-pillars/?fbclid=IwAR0m_atvZEj5RqG0EVFtRyXfsUYhT9Oo_VuGPhnJ-3pFGTPRK9uN08Vh0sg\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.kerbalspaceprogram.com/dev-diaries/developer-insights-3-ksp2-design-pillars/?fbclid=IwAR0m_atvZEj5RqG0EVFtRyXfsUYhT9Oo_VuGPhnJ-3pFGTPRK9uN08Vh0sg\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"shdwlrd","CreatedById":113880,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-16T17:10:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLiked that they shared their intentions for colony operations.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpaceFace545","CreatedById":196943,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-16T17:31:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey could have given us a bit of gameplay after nearly two months\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dirkidirk","CreatedById":200064,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-16T17:31:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nnice\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-04-16T17:57:13Z\u0022 title=\u002204/16/2020 05:57  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EApril 16, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Dirkidirk\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MrFancyPL","CreatedById":94843,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-16T18:38:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223771841\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022193177\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221587058283\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022196943\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SpaceFace545\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, SpaceFace545 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey could have given us a bit of gameplay after nearly two months\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think that\u0027s their way to express \u0022We are not ready\u0022. I\u0027m kinda sad because of this, but that is understandable.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"justspace103","CreatedById":64088,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-16T18:45:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI love how they adressed the\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\u0022\u003E balance b\u003C/span\u003Eetween crazy micromanagement and simple on the colonies. what even better is that enven though you may disagree with their choices of making colonies say \u0022too easy\u0022 it seems like they will be making the process such as resource gathering extremly modable so that would be great.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, they did say \u0022We all know that Kerbals just need cool suits, \u003Cstrong\u003Esnacks\u003C/strong\u003E, and something fun to crash.\u0022\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#666666;font-size:17px;\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003ECould it be that there is going to be a sort of semi-simple life support system for keeping kerbals entertined on colonies? this would be awesome, but i could also see that this could be beyond the scope of the game. maybe it will be easily modable\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-04-16T18:46:13Z\u0022 title=\u002204/16/2020 06:46  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EApril 16, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by justspace103\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpaceFace545","CreatedById":196943,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-16T18:47:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223771869\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022193177\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221587062326\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002294843\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022MrFancyPL\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 minutes ago, MrFancyPL said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think that\u0027s their way to express \u0022We are not ready\u0022. I\u0027m kinda sad because of this, but that is understandable.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut they probably have pictures, like our hype has depression and now it needs meds\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kaerbanogue","CreatedById":189143,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-16T19:09:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223771874\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022193177\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221587062726\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002264088\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022justspace103\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, justspace103 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, they did say \u0022We all know that Kerbals just need cool suits, \u003Cstrong\u003Esnacks\u003C/strong\u003E, and something fun to crash.\u0022\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:rgb(255,255,255);color:rgb(102,102,102);font-size:17px;\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003ECould it be that there is going to be a sort of semi-simple life support system for keeping kerbals entertined on colonies?\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think they are just referring to the snack compartiment, visible inside ksp pods\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223771841\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022193177\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221587058283\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022196943\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SpaceFace545\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, SpaceFace545 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey could have given us a bit of gameplay after nearly two months\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou know something is happening in the world ? They are giving us news, noticing us they are currently working and giving us more infos on ksp 2. [snip]\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-04-16T23:07:23Z\u0022 title=\u002204/16/2020 11:07  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EApril 16, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Vanamonde\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HansonKerman","CreatedById":185809,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-16T19:14:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223771874\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022193177\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221587062726\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002264088\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022justspace103\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n28 minutes ago, justspace103 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCould it be that there is going to be a sort of semi-simple life support system for keeping kerbals entertined on colonies? this would be awesome, but i could also see that this could be beyond the scope of the game. maybe it will be easily moddable\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Lucida Sans Unicode\u0027, \u0027Lucida Grande\u0027, sans-serif;\u0022\u003Ethat would be cool\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223771888\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022193177\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221587064150\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022189143\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kaerbanogue\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 minutes ago, Kaerbanogue said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think they are just referring to the snack compartiment, visible inside ksp pods\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Lucida Sans Unicode\u0027, \u0027Lucida Grande\u0027, sans-serif;\u0022\u003Ehmmm\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Lucida Sans Unicode\u0027, \u0027Lucida Grande\u0027, sans-serif;\u0022\u003Espeaking of IVA, I do hope that IVA is still detailed and working\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-16T19:17:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI eat this kind of stuff up. I love snapshots into developers\u0027 thought processes. Thanks!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was a bit uncomfortable about the game becoming like Fallout 4 where every time you (or at least I) encountered a settlement there was almost a visceral reaction to the amount of micromanaging busywork required to keep them happy. Really? 20 new people arrived and not one of you thought to cobble together some beds for them? I like that the focus is staying on rockets and how colonies can help them, and not vice versa.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kaerbanogue","CreatedById":189143,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-16T19:20:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223771892\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022193177\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221587064462\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022185809\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022HansonKerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, HansonKerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Lucida Sans Unicode\u0027, \u0027Lucida Grande\u0027, sans-serif;\u0022\u003Espeaking of IVA, I do hope that IVA is still detailed and working\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYea boi that\u0027s my #1 most wanted feature. Did you know there is a very good mod for functionnal IVAs for KSP ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLink in case:\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022199038\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed3227676228\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/186715-18x-de_ivaextension-for-all-the-stock-pod-ivas/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:211px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-16T19:27:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey stuck with colonies.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dirkidirk","CreatedById":200064,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-16T19:30:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223771903\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022193177\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221587065237\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022#\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/a\u003E \u003Cspan\u003EHide contents\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey stuck with colonies.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nyeah, they did...\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:8px;\u0022\u003Ethere is probably some joke here that I didn\u0027t catch.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nwhat is happening in this thread!?!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have spent all of my likes here.\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-04-16T19:31:11Z\u0022 title=\u002204/16/2020 07:31  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EApril 16, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Dirkidirk\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cokeblob11","CreatedById":204035,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-16T19:57:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223771874\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022193177\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221587062726\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002264088\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022justspace103\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, justspace103 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, they did say \u0022We all know that Kerbals just need cool suits, \u003Cstrong\u003Esnacks\u003C/strong\u003E, and something fun to crash.\u0022\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#666666;font-size:17px;\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003ECould it be that there is going to be a sort of semi-simple life support system for keeping kerbals entertined on colonies?\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you look at most of the big interplanetary/stellar ships they\u0027ve shown in trailers so far, most of them have these triangular containers, this could be ore but I\u0027m guessing its something like \u0022snacks\u0022 that are necessary to keep kerbals alive for long periods of time.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SkyHook","CreatedById":31496,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-16T20:47:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m glad they are putting a lot of thought into this mechanic. One of the biggest missing pieces was the \u0022why\u0022 of landing rockets on all of the worlds in the original game, and the colony system will go a long way toward answering that question. Creating orbital drydocks and surface colonies with ACTUAL game mechanics driving them will be a joy! KSP2 when!?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-04-16T20:47:38Z\u0022 title=\u002204/16/2020 08:47  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EApril 16, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by SkyHook\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mcwaffles2003","CreatedById":180102,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-16T22:10:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223771841\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022193177\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221587058283\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022196943\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SpaceFace545\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, SpaceFace545 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey could have given us a bit of gameplay after nearly two months\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/OUnOyY0bJk0?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s been barely a month....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-04-16T22:10:51Z\u0022 title=\u002204/16/2020 10:10  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EApril 16, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by mcwaffles2003\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SpaceFace545","CreatedById":196943,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-16T23:01:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223771989\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022193177\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221587075028\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022180102\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mcwaffles2003\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n50 minutes ago, mcwaffles2003 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022#\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/a\u003E \u003Cspan\u003EHide contents\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/OUnOyY0bJk0?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s been barely a month....\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI was saying since the last dev blog but taking time to got to pax east probably cut into their time budget\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-16T23:08:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSome comments have been removed or edited. There\u0027s no need to attack each other over this.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HansonKerman","CreatedById":185809,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-17T00:39:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223771896\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022193177\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221587064842\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022189143\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kaerbanogue\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, Kaerbanogue said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYea boi that\u0027s my #1 most wanted feature. Did you know there is a very good mod for functionnal IVAs for KSP ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Lucida Sans Unicode\u0027, \u0027Lucida Grande\u0027, sans-serif;\u0022\u003Eyou say that like they don\u2019t exist. For a very long time, IVA\u2019s blurry numbers were the only way to get AGL info. You can also control throttle, look at a bigger navball, check the atmosphere, etc. waiting for a staging and joystick button so that some mad lad will do an only stock iva playthrough in KSP2\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mattinoz","CreatedById":118580,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-17T04:35:38Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223771874\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022193177\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221587062726\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002264088\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022justspace103\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 hours ago, justspace103 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI love how they adressed the\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\u0022\u003E balance b\u003C/span\u003Eetween crazy micromanagement and simple on the colonies. what even better is that enven though you may disagree with their choices of making colonies say \u0022too easy\u0022 it seems like they will be making the process such as resource gathering extremly modable so that would be great.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, they did say \u0022We all know that Kerbals just need cool suits, \u003Cstrong\u003Esnacks\u003C/strong\u003E, and something fun to crash.\u0022\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#666666;font-size:17px;\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003ECould it be that there is going to be a sort of semi-simple life support system for keeping kerbals entertined on colonies? this would be awesome, but i could also see that this could be beyond the scope of the game. maybe it will be easily modable\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI read that with hope as well. especially in the context of flying missions to make colonies self sufficient. How can they be self sufficient without something to run out of.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis whole dev note fills me with hope for the game.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"OOM","CreatedById":199309,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-17T07:04:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223771925\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022193177\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221587067056\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022204035\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Cokeblob11\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n11 hours ago, Cokeblob11 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you look at most of the big interplanetary/stellar ships they\u0027ve shown in trailers so far, most of them have these triangular containers, this could be ore but I\u0027m guessing its something like \u0022snacks\u0022 that are necessary to keep kerbals alive for long periods of time.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere may be more than just snacks. But also the necessary materials to create a colony, too.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-04-17T07:04:19Z\u0022 title=\u002204/17/2020 07:04  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EApril 17, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by OOM\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HenryBlatbugIII","CreatedById":159624,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-17T07:22:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nQuote\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe want players to build crazy orbital drydocks and mining colonies on stalactites.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI hope that\u0027s not a typo, because that means that some planets are going to be significantly more interesting than I expected.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(Spikes on the ground are stalagmites.\u00A0 Spikes hanging from the ceiling of a cave are stalactites.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kaerbanogue","CreatedById":189143,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-17T07:41:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223772038\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022193177\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221587083984\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022185809\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022HansonKerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, HansonKerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Lucida Sans Unicode\u0027, \u0027Lucida Grande\u0027, sans-serif;\u0022\u003Eyou say that like they don\u2019t exist. For a very long time, IVA\u2019s blurry numbers were the only way to get AGL info. You can also control throttle, look at a bigger navball, check the atmosphere, etc. waiting for a staging and joystick button so that some mad lad will do an only stock iva playthrough in KSP2\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0I know that but I won\u0027t say IVAs are fonctionnal in KSP...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTry flying on instruments and you will know your pain !\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:/\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/ZNGIcon1.png\u0022 title=\u0022:/\u0022\u003E\u00A0 Personnaly I love aircrafts and clickable cockpits are my thing. Knowing speed, altitude and attitude precisely is necessary to fly properly an aircraft. Moreover with the current status of IVAs, trying to launch and land on the mun, for exemple, only in first person, without mods nor watching the map is harder in ksp than IRL ! (If you know how to use real-life spacecraft instruments)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut maybe someone whose gameplay is more focused on building than flying won\u0027t be bothered at all by the lack of instrumentations inside KSP pods. So I think that depends on your gameplay style...\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223772146\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022193177\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221587108137\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022159624\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022HenryBlatbugIII\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 minutes ago, HenryBlatbugIII said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI hope that\u0027s not a typo, because that means that some planets are going to be significantly more interesting than I expected.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWow I didn\u0027t see that ! We need caves, hope that\u0027s indeed a hint, not a typo !\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"The Aziz","CreatedById":150811,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-17T09:00:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223772151\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022193177\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221587109275\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022189143\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kaerbanogue\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Kaerbanogue said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223772146\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022193177\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221587108137\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022159624\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022HenryBlatbugIII\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, HenryBlatbugIII said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI hope that\u0027s not a typo, because that means that some planets are going to be significantly more interesting than I expected.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWow I didn\u0027t see that ! We need caves, hope that\u0027s indeed a hint, not a typo !\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUh umm, I\u0027m just gonna point (again) at one piece of Developer Insights #1\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#666666;font-size:17px;\u0022\u003EIn the meantime, we\u2019re still hard at work in the radness mines, discovering and extracting new veins of totally sweet gameplay. I\u2019m very sorry for this last sentence, but I\u2019m leaving it in.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCall me crazy if that wasn\u0027t first hint.\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mcwaffles2003","CreatedById":180102,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-04-17T09:30:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223772164\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022193177\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221587114055\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150811\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022The Aziz\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n26 minutes ago, The Aziz said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUh umm, I\u0027m just gonna point (again) at one piece of Developer Insights #1\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThats just a phrase, caves wont be possible with the height mapping being used, nor overhanging ledges\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}